unittitle.value: Time Inc. <title render="italic">The March of Time</title> Audiovisual Collection

abstract.value: The Time Inc. <title render="italic">The March of Time</title> Audiovisual Collection contains internal and commercially distributed audiovisual materials that were produced by <title render="italic">The March of Time</title>, a division of Time Inc. The materials were created between 1979 and 1995.

p.value: Unreformatted audiovisual and digital material in the collection are not accessible. As the entire collection is audiovisual, it is all restricted at this time. Materials are stored offsite.
This collection should be cited as Time Inc. <title render="italic">The March of Time</title> Audiovisual Collection, MS 3009-RG 15, New-York Historical Society.
Prendergast, Curtis, and Geoffrey Colvin. 1986. The World of Time Inc.: The Intimate History of a Changing Enterprise, 1960-1980. New York: Atheneum.
Unreformatted audiovisual and digital material in the collection is not accessible.

dsc.value:
Series I. Audiovisual Materials for Internal Use [RESTRICTED]11 Linear feetin 11 record cartons1979-1995, undatedScope and Contents

The Internal Use series contains videocassettes that were created for use within Time Inc. or for preservation purposes. These tapes mainly contain episodes of The March of Time but Time Warner: The Changing Face of Media and Entertainment is assumed to contain only clips from The March of Time. While the majority of tapes contain episodes from one volume, some tapes include episodes from multiple volumes.

Arrangement

Arranged in their original order by volume number and with special releases at the end. If a tape includes episodes from multiple volumes then that tape is placed with the earliest volume on the tape.
